cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the use of altmetric data for measuring societal impact of scientific papers, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves analyzing data from various sources, including F1000, which could be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI). The normalization of altmetric data is also discussed, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SD) where normalization techniques are commonly used.
